content.raw:
[The Jenkins build in Xenial](https://build.osrfoundation.org/job/gazebo_experimental-ci-pr_any-xenial-amd64-gpu-none/). There are some cppcheck warnings, most of the them come probably from default branch, not sure if any of them is introduced by these changes.

The thing compiles fine for me under Xenial docker, tests are passing, valgrind is happy. I like the design to place different instances adjacently in memory, it can be a good performance improvement.
